pub fn gc_minor(
  &mut self,
  roots: &mut [FzValue],
  mailbox: &mut VecDeque<FzValue>,
) {
  // from_ranges = [(young_start, young_top)] only.
  // For each FzValue in roots[] and mailbox that is a heap pointer:
  //   if ptr in young range → copy to old_top (bump old_top), install FORWARDED_KIND, update slot
  //   if ptr in old range → leave unchanged (old object, already valid)
  // BFS scan of newly copied objects in old space:
  //   for each child pointer:
  //     young child → copy to old, forward
  //     old child → pass through (from_range check fails, no forward)
  // Reset young_top = young_start.
  // Update last_minor_live_bytes = bytes promoted to old this cycle.
  // Increment minor_gc_count.
}

The existing forward_field() and cheney_forward() functions already implement the from_range check. gc_minor() is gc() with from_ranges restricted to the young block and to-space being the old block (bump into old_top rather than a fresh block). No new forwarding logic needed.

For park-time minor GC: roots = [parked_cont as FzValue] (mailbox empty at park time).

Tests: young object reachable from root survives minor GC and is now in old block. Young object not reachable is collected. Old-space pointer in root is left untouched. new→old pointer in a young object: young object promoted, pointer to old object preserved unchanged. minor_gc_count incremented after each call.
